                                                                           }
                                                          },
                                                          {
                                                              "mark":  {
                                                                           "type":  "text",
                                                                           "align":  "left",
                                                                           "baseline":  "top",
                                                                           "font":  "Inter, \u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Arial, sans-serif",
                                                                           "fontSize":  12,
                                                                           "color":  "#333333",
                                                                           "text":  [
                                                                                        "This narrative shifts our entire understanding of the oral health crisis. The data tells a story of an epidemic that is",
                                                                                        "migrating into urban centers, capturing the youth, and strongly anchoring itself among the working male population. To combat",
                                                                                        "the rising tides of oral mucosal lesions and pre-cancer, healthcare strategies must move away from generic campaigns and",
                                                                                        "focus heavily on urban youth spaces, workplace wellness initiatives, and targeted male-centric public health interventions.",
                                                                                        "Without immediate action, the cultural habits of today will inevitably become the oncology statistics of tomorrow."
                                                                                    ],
